{"lemma":"بَقِيَّةُ","slug":"بَقِيَّةُ","root":"ب.ق.#","root_slug":"ب-ق-_","root_link":"/words/roots/ب-ق-_","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n3048","n3053"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A8%D9%8E%D9%82%D9%90%D9%8A%D9%8E%D9%91%D8%A9%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"rest, remainder","examples":[{"text":"وَأَسْفَرَتِ ٱلْعَمَلِيَّةُ ٱلَّتِي نَفَّذَتْهَا ٱلْمُخَابَرَاتُ ٱلْعِرَاقِيَّةُ وِفْقَ ٱلْبَيَانِ عَنِ «ٱعْتِقَالِ بَعْضِ ٱلْخَاطِفِينَ وَقَتْلِ أَحَدِهِمْ خِلَالَهَا، وَتَتِّمُ مُلَاحَقَةُ بَقِيَّةِ أَفْرَادِ ٱلْعِصَابَةِ».","english":"And the operation which the Iraqi intelligence carried out, led, according to the statement, to “the arrest of a deal of the kidnappers and to the killing of one of them during the course of it, and the pursuit of the rest of the individuals of the gang is proceeding.”"}]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ba.qij.ja/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n3048","headword_ar":"بَقْيَةٌ","root":"bqY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baqiy~apN","text_ar":"بَقِيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n3053","headword_ar":"بَقِيَّةٌ","root":"bqY","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A remain, remainder, remaining portion, remnant, relic, residue,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"remains,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rest,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a thing; (KL, PS, &c.;) a subst. from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baqiYa","text_ar":"بَقِىَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as signifying “ it remained over and above, ” and “ it remained behind: ” pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baqaAyaA","text_ar":"بَقَايَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baqiy~aAtN","text_ar":"بَقِيَّاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAqiyapN","text_ar":"بَاقِيَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", also, [pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bawaAqK","text_ar":"بَوَاقٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAqiyaAtN","text_ar":"بَاقِيَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] has the same meaning as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baqiy~apN","text_ar":"بَقِيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) [i. e., as explained above; and so has ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAqK","text_ar":"بَاقٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aYo'K baAqK","text_ar":"شَىْءٍ بَاقٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.] You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baqiYa mina Al$~aYo'i baqiy~apN","text_ar":"بَقِىَ مِنَ الشَّىْءِ بَقِيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[explained before: see 1]. (S.) [And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"humo baqiy~apu Als~ayofi","text_ar":"هُمْ بَقِيَّةُ السَّيْفِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baqaAyaA Als~ayofi","text_ar":"بَقَايَا السَّيْفِ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They are those who have been spared by the sword"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN mino baqiy~api Alqawomi","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ مِنْ بَقِيَّةِ القَوْمِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is of the best of the people,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"company of men:"},{"kind":"text","text":"because a man reserves the most excellent of the things that he produces. (Bd in xi. 118.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN mino baqiy~api A^aholihi","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ مِنْ بَقِيَّةِ اَهْلِهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is of the most excellent of his people,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"family."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham p. 78.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN baqiy~apu Alqawomi","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ بَقِيَّةُ القَوْمِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is the best of the people,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"company of men:"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baqaAyaA","text_ar":"بَقَايَا"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Kull p. 96.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uwluw baqiy~apK","text_ar":"اُولُو بَقِيَّةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur xi. 118, hence means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Persons possessed of excellence:"},{"kind":"text","text":"[see a phrase mentioned voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"balalN","text_ar":"بَلَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"possessing a relic of judgment and intelligence:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"persons of religion and excellence:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Jel:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"persons of understanding"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and discrimination:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"persons of obedience:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having the quality of preserving themselves"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Az, Bd, K, *)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from punishment,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by their holding the approved religion:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Az, TA:) and this last explanation is confirmed by another reading, which is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AwlwA baqoyapK","text_ar":"اولوا بَقْيَةٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"possessing a quality of watching,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"observing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and hence,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of guarding,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"preserving"},{"kind":"text","text":"];"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baqoyap","text_ar":"بَقْيَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"being the inf. n. of un. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baqaAhu","text_ar":"بَقَاهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaboqiyhi","text_ar":"يَبْقِيهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", signifying “ he watched, ” or “ observed, ” &c., “ him, ” or “ it. ” (Bd.) See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buqayaA","text_ar":"بُقَيَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baqiy~apN","text_ar":"بَقِيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also a subst. from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aboqayotu maA bayonanaA","text_ar":"اَبْقَيْتُ مَا بَيْنَنَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[explained before: see 4: app. meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Forbearance from marring much,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"exceedingly, the state of unity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of amity, subsisting between two persons,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"parties:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and such may be its meaning in the phrase above-mentioned ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AwlwA bqy~p","text_ar":"اولوا بقيّة"},{"kind":"text","text":")]. (K.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baqiy~apu A@ll~`hi","text_ar":"بَقِيَّةُ ا@للّٰهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur xi. 87, [after the command, in the next preceding verse, to give full measure and weight,] means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God's sustenance that remains for you"},{"kind":"text","text":"after your giving full measure [and weight]: (Jel:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that which God has preserved for you, of what is lawful,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr, Bd,) after [your] keeping aloof from that which he has forbidden you: (Bd:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the good state,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"condition, remaining for you:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Zj, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the fear"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muraAqabap","text_ar":"مُرَاقَبَة"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of God;"},{"kind":"text","text":"accord. to some: (Fr, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the obedience of God, and"},{"kind":"text","text":"(as Aboo-'Alee says, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the looking for his recompense:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baqiy~apN","text_ar":"بَقِيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAqiyapN","text_ar":"بَاقِيَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any religious service whereby one seeks to obtain the recompense of God;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and such is the meaning of the former in this instance. (Er-Rághib, TA.) ―         -b5-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAqiyapN","text_ar":"بَاقِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["Msb","Bd","Jel","K","TA","Az","Fr","Zj"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}